  "text": "The ideas have been implemented in UCLID [CITATION_1] ], a platform for modeling and verifying infinite-state systems. Although we demonstrate the ideas in the context of this tool and the logic (CLU) it supports, the ideas developed here are not strongly tied to this logic. We conclude by describing our use of predicate abstraction to verify several hardware and software systems, including a directory-based cache coherence protocol devised by Steven German [German] . We believe we are the first to verify the protocol for a system with an unbounded number of clients, each communicating via unbounded FIFO channels.",
